"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156142","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-29","<p>In Financial Year 2018-19, 65,759 HM Forces Railcards were issued to those who are eligible, each of which is valid for 12 months.</p>","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","4956","2019-10-29T15:21:58.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156142/answer","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156142/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-24","Railways: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many active HM Forces Railcards there are.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","4955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156143","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-29","<p>The Ministry of Justice is committed to ensuring effective support to families bereaved by murder and manslaughter. To ensure that these families are appropriately supported, whether the homicide takes place at home or abroad, we have provided up to £3.4m per annum in funding to deliver the Homicide Service.</p><p> </p><p>Families bereaved by violent crime can access the Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme where the crime was committed in Great Britain, or the Victims of Overseas Terrorism Compensation Scheme where the crime was a terrorist attack committed overseas. Further, where the crime was committed in an EU member state, it may be possible for families to access any compensation scheme that the member state has under the EU Compensation Directive or the Council of Europe Convention on Compensation for Victims of Violent Crime.</p><p> </p><p>A review of the Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme is underway, looking at its scope, and eligibility rules and requirements. The recommendations of the Victims’ Commissioner in her report on the entitlements and experiences of bereaved families following homicide abroad will be considered carefully as part of this review.</p>","Aldridge-Brownhills","Wendy Morton",,"2019-10-29T17:38:11.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156143/answer","Biography information for Wendy Morton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156143/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-24","British Nationals Abroad: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to ensure that families whose loved ones are murdered abroad have access to criminal injuries compensation.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","4922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156144","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-29","<p>In Financial Year 2018-19, 65,759 HM Forces Railcards were issued to those who are eligible, each of which is valid for 12 months.</p>","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","4955","2019-10-29T15:21:58.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156144/answer","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156144/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-24","Railways: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many serving personnel use the HM Forces Railcard.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","4956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156145","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-29","<p>All training offered to foreign military personnel is provided in accordance with an Overseas Security and Justice Assistance (OSJA) assessment, which will evaluate the risk of the training being used in a way that is not in line with human rights and British values. Participation in UK training exposes personnel from other countries to UK values and standards and helps to promote concepts of accountability, transparency and human rights protection. OSJA assessments are reviewed annually and also if there is a change of circumstances which might significantly alter the risks relating to any existing Defence training programmes.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-10-29T15:25:08.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156145/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156145/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-24","Military Aid: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will review his Department's policy on training military officers from countries with a record of human rights abuses.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","5051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156146","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-11-01","<p>The law was changed on 1 November 2018 to allow clinicians on the General Medical Council’s ‘Specialist Register’ to prescribe cannabis-based products for medicinal use, where clinically appropriate and in the best interest of patients. The Government has been clear that decisions on whether to prescribe these products must remain a clinical one.</p><p> </p><p>Following a meeting in Parliament with the families of patients seeking access to medicinal cannabis, my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care asked NHS England and NHS Improvement to undertake a rapid process review into any barriers to prescribing on the National Health Service, where clinically appropriate. The review report is now published and the Department is working closely with NHS England and NHS Improvement and other delivery partners to implement the report’s recommendations. This includes promoting more high-quality research through the publicly funded National Institute for Health Research to develop the evidence base and exploring alternative studies to help children and young adults with treatment resistance epilepsy who are currently receiving cannabis-based medicines. We have also contacted all producers of cannabis-based products, known to have an interest in supplying the United Kingdom market, to encourage and support research applications to develop the evidence base further.</p><p> </p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-11-01T12:17:20.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156146/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156146/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-24","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what progress has been made for the provision of medical cannabis on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Alberto Costa","South Leicestershire","Alberto Costa","5043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156147","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-29","<p>I am committed to improving access at all stations. Last year we published the Inclusive Transport Strategy which sets out what we are doing to improve access across all transport modes. As part of this, we extended our Access for All programme with an additional £300m of funding. This provides accessibility improvements over and above those required by the rail industry itself. Stations are nominated by the rail industry bodies who can work alongside local authorities and Members of Parliament. Stations are selected for funding through a prioritisation and assessment process. Sandbach was not nominated for this funding.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to seek further opportunities, and funding, to make more improvements.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-10-29T16:00:33.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156147/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156147/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-24","Sandbach Station: Access","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to ensure that increasing accessibility at Sandbach railway station is included in the Government's disability action plan.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156148","Home Office","false","2019-11-05","<p>Essex police are carrying out their investigation at pace including assessing the background of the circumstances of the victims in the tragic event at Grays.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-11-05T17:01:43.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156148/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156148/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-24","Human Trafficking: Essex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an assessment of the background circumstances of the 39 Chinese nationals found killed in Grays, Essex on 23 October 2019 including the possibility that the victims were (a) Uyghur Muslims or members of another religious or ethnic minority group in China seeking asylum in the UK or (b) victims of modern slavery being trafficked for the purposes of economic exploitation by organised criminal groups.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","4966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156149","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-29","<p>We carefully consider each request for funding. Memorial 2007 approached MHCLG last year and unfortunately the Department was unable to provide support at that time. We are supportive of the aims of the monument and the organisation. The suffering caused by slavery and the slave trade is among the most dishonourable and abhorrent chapters in human history. The International Slavery Museum in Liverpool is an example of a memorial that educates citizens about this dark time in our shared history.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-29T17:51:16.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156149/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156149/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-24","Slavery: Monuments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking help ensure that Memorial 2007 has the necessary funding required before November 2019.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","4952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156150","Home Office","false","2019-11-05","<p><strong><em>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Dissolution.</em></strong></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-11-05T17:05:13.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156150/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156150/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-24","Asylum, Migration and Integration Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to continue to allocate money to the Government's Asylum, Migration and Integration Fund in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","5020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156151","Treasury","false","2019-10-29","<p>The Royal Mint has paused production of the coin to mark the UK’s exit from the EU.</p><p> </p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-10-29T13:47:34.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156151/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156151/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-24","Coinage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether work has commenced on minting the 50 pence coin to mark the UK's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","4962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156152","Women and Equalities","false","2019-10-31","<p>The Period Poverty Taskforce has made excellent progress in bringing together organisations such as the PSHE Association from the public sector, the phs group from the private sector, Bloody Good Period from the third sector and other experts to tackle period poverty in the UK. The Taskforce and its composite workstreams have met twice and begun to identify: access barriers and the groups that are most affected by them; a programme of work to tackle stigma and shame surrounding menstruation; and research priorities to improve the evidence surrounding period poverty and menstrual stigma in the UK.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-10-31T09:32:06.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156152/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156152/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2019-10-24","Period Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what progress has been made by the joint taskforce on period poverty on bringing together  (a) public, (b) private and (c) third sector organisations to tackle period poverty.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","5037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156153","Department for Education","false","2019-10-29","<p>Evidence suggests that some learners in England may be missing education due to difficulties in managing their periods. Periods should not be a barrier to education for any learner, and the department is introducing this scheme to help state-funded primary and secondary schools and 16-19 institutions respond to the needs of learners in the way that is most appropriate to their circumstances.</p><p>Nationwide rollout of this scheme to all state-funded primary and secondary schools and 16-19 institutions will take place in early 2020. To help state-funded primary and secondary schools and 16-19 institutions implement the scheme, the department will publish guidance later this year.</p>","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan",,"2019-10-29T14:07:05.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156153/answer","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156153/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-10-24","Pupils: Sanitary Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Spring Statement 2019, what the timeframe is for the roll-out of free sanitary products in (a) primary schools, (b) secondary schools and (c) further education colleges.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","5038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156154","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-11-04","<p>The Government recognises the critical role that post offices play in communities and for small businesses across the UK. This is why the Government committed to safeguard the post office network and protect existing rural services. The overall number of post offices across the UK remains at its most stable in decades with over 11,500 branches thanks to significant Government investment of over £2 billion since 2010.</p><p>While the Government sets the strategic direction for the Post Office, it allows the company the commercial freedom to deliver this strategy as an independent business. Whether the Post Office is accredited is an operational matter for Post Office Limited. I have therefore asked Nick Read the Group Chief Executive of Post Office Limited, to write to the hon Member on this matter. A copy of his reply will be placed in the Libraries of the House.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2019-11-04T11:15:28.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156154/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156154/answer","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156154/answer/previousversion/2599","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-24","Post Office: Credit Cards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Post Office is accredited under the Payment Card Industry Security Standards Council.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156155","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-10-29","<p>The Business Readiness Fund was set up to help to prepare businesses for leaving the EU on 31 October. £10.6M has been approved across 139 successful bids, with just under £10.2M already paid to Business Representative Organisations. Applications have spanned a wide range of sectors, with organisations delivering activity across all regions of the UK. A list of all successful organisations will be released in due course.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-10-29T14:26:01.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156155/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156155/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-24","Brexit: Chester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of the Brexit Readiness Fund has been allocated to Chester.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","5039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156156","Department for Education","false","2019-10-29","<p>The funds in apprenticeship service accounts are available for levy-paying employers to use for 24 months before they begin to expire on a rolling, month-by-month basis. We have never anticipated that levy-payers will use all the funds available to them, but they are able to if they wish. Individual levy-paying employers have full control over when and where apprenticeship funds are spent to meet their current and future skills needs.</p><p>Employers’ levy funds are distinct from the Department for Education’s ring-fenced annual apprenticeship budget. This budget is set on an annual basis to cover the costs of all apprenticeships. This includes new apprenticeships in both levy-paying employers and those that do not pay the levy, as well as existing apprenticeships for learners who started in previous years. As this budget is distinct from the funds in employers’ apprenticeship service accounts, it is not affected by the value of any funds which may expire from employers’ accounts each month.</p>","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan",,"2019-10-29T13:58:33.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156156/answer","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156156/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-10-24","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether unspent apprenticeship levy monies returned to his Department are allocated to the apprenticeship budget for use by non-levy paying employers.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","4925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156157","Women and Equalities","false","2019-10-31","<p>The Government Equalities Office will publish research on engaging men and boys on gender expectations, attitudes and behaviours early next year as planned.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-10-31T09:29:47.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156157/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156157/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2019-10-24","Males: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, when she plans to publish research commissioned into the stereotypical expectations of men and boys announced on 19 November 2018.","false","Biography information for Mrs Maria Miller","Basingstoke","Mrs Maria Miller","4951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156158","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-29","<p>Towns were chosen on the basis of a robust selection methodology. This took into account various qualitative and quantitative indicators including income deprivation, skills, productivity, EU exit exposure, economic shocks, investment opportunities, and policy alignment.</p><p>The government is unable to publish the full selection methodology used to choose the 100 Towns that will work towards Town Deals at this time. This is because it includes information that relates to the formulation and development of government policy which is still live and ongoing. It will also feed into and inform future funding policy, including the competitive element of the Towns Fund.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-29T16:24:03.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156158/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156158/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-24","Stronger Towns Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will publish (a) the full selection methodology used to allocate monies from the Stronger Towns Fund and (b) the score awarded to each applicant.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","5028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156159","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-29","<p>The number of band 3-5 prison officers employed in each prison is provided in the accompanying excel file. Data is provided as at 30 June 2010 and 2019.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, 21 prisons have closed and one prison has transferred to private sector operation, which has an impact on the figures. In addition, 3 establishments (HMP The Wolds, HMP Birmingham and Medway Secure Training Centre) have transferred to public sector operation.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-10-29T14:59:13.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156159/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1156159/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-24","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers worked at each prison in (a) 2010 and (b) 2019.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","5058"
