"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151845","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-28","<p>Any additional costs related to the delay to the delivery of Audacious have been contained within the current Astute Equipment Programme budget.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-10-28T15:18:10.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151845/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151845/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-23","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to public purse is of the delay to the delivery of HMS Audacious and other Astute-class nuclear submarines; and whether funding will be (a) reduced or (b) withheld from other defence projects to fund additional costs.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","4356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151846","Home Office","false","2019-10-28","<p>It is the duty of any responsible Government to prepare for every eventuality including the scenario that we leave the EU without agreeing a deal.</p><p>With that in mind, we are working closely with operational partners - including the police - on contingency planning so we can ensure the safety and security of our citizens in all scenarios.</p><p>Police Forces are working closely with partner agencies in local areas. Decisions on the deployment of police resources are matters for individual Chief Officers.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","4359","2019-10-28T17:10:48.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151846/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151846/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-23","Ports: Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans there are for police officers to provide support at ports in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","4357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151847","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence has not placed any additional personnel on standby to provide support to ports throughout the UK for Brexit. However, Defence has developed a prudent standby package of 3,300 Defence personnel who are on standby to support civil authorities on a range of tasks if required.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","4360","2019-10-28T16:27:37.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151847/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151847/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-23","Military Aid: Ports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans there are for military personnel to provide support at ports in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","4358"
